This paper focuses on semantic segmentation using 3D LiDAR data, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves incorporating human domain knowledge into a neural network model, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions using a rule-based classifier, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL, in that order.
